			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Cloudmark is a profitable, privately-held anti-spam technology company that produces high performance messaging security solutions to the world&rsquo;s largest ISPs, mobile and social networks, located in San Francisco, California. Our customers include over 100 of the world&#39;s largest Internet service providers, including the majority of tier-1 operators in North America, Japan and Europe. Our products protect more than one billion inboxes, worldwide.<br />
<br />
<strong>Objective of Position</strong><br />
The Program Director&#39;s objective is to help architect, then deploy, any one (or all) of Cloudmark&rsquo;s solutions into a contracted customer. In addition to deployment, the Program Director may well also be involved in management of policies and operational elements of the said customer.<br />
<br />
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;Deployment of Cloudmark data applications in fixed or mobile operators networks.</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Provide input on architecture and design options, operational concepts, and application acceptance test plan.</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Planning and design of TCP/IP based solutions with wireless components.</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Solution documentation and authoring of technical white papers.</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Network analysis and decoding of TCP/IP and data stacks in troubleshooting scenarios.</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Deployment support for both customers and partners</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Assist and deploy trials and prototypes</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Manage integration projects and roll-out</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;Strong knowledge of Mobile Architectures is mandatory; SS7 Network Architectures (ideally), Mobile Internet/Broadband Architectures</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Strong knowledge of Mobile Messaging architectures is mandatory; SMS, MMS</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Knowledge of Internet architectures is desirable; Email (SMTP), Broadband (IP Core)</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Linux and UNIX skills; Thorough knowledge of Linux and UNIX application deployment</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Experience in implementing carrier grade client-server applications in a commercial environment</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Systems integration expertise with TCP/IP skills in data networking and internetworking</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Configuration/installation of Cisco/Nortel switches, routers, and load balancers</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Good knowledge of LAN network infrastructure: security, routing, network management, performance management</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Able to analyze HTTP, HTTPS, POP, IMAP, FTP, SNMP, and other data traffic</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Can configure VLAN&#39;s, GRE, and VPN tunnels</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Familiar with development processes and lifecycles</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Can travel abroad on short notice</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Can produce clear and accurate solution low level diagrams</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Able to understand customer requirements and translate to development and product management teams</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Ability to produce succinct technical design documentation and test plans</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
&nbsp; <strong>Education</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;Bachelor&#39;s degree in datacoms/telecoms or equivalent.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>&nbsp; Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;Experience in implementing mobile data applications</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Mobile network design and configuration</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Previous experience with systems integrators, consultancy firms, and/or professional services environments</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Experience working with remote multicultural multi skilled internal teams and customers</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Broad understanding of WAN network infrastructure and protocols (Frame, ATM, MPLS, ISDN)</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Broad understanding of mobile network infrastructure (2.5 and 3G, GPRS, UMTS)</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Good knowledge of mobile data traffic and mobile data devices</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Special Training</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;Cisco CCNP certification, F5 or similar</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Skills Required</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;Understanding of Anti-Spam/messaging technologies (SMTP, SMS, MSS) market</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Excellent listening skills</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Excellent presentation skills</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Extremely well organized and &lsquo;self-starter&rsquo;</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Ability to think on your feet</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Fast learner</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Good technical account management and project management skills</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Ability to manage complex integration projects</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Ability to juggle multiple priorities</li>
<li>
&nbsp;Solutions, consultative selling style</li>
</ul>
