			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Cloudmark is a profitable, privately-held anti-spam technology company that produces high performance messaging security solutions to the world&rsquo;s largest ISPs, mobile and social networks, located in San Francisco, California. Our customers include over 100 of the world&#39;s largest Internet service providers, including the majority of tier-1 operators in North America, Japan and Europe. Our products protect more than one billion inboxes, worldwide.</p>
<p>
Objective of Position</p>
<p>
At Cloudmark, research isn&rsquo;t simply data collection &ndash; it&rsquo;s bringing facts to life for our customers, partners and internal team. To do this, we need a senior security researcher who is a first-rate knowledge-builder with a talent for uncovering, analyzing, and synthesizing information from a variety of sources to position Cloudmark as the industry thought leader and expand our voice through the media and analyst community, as well as other channels.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities:<br />
&bull; Threat research and analysis<br />
&bull; Media spokesperson<br />
&bull; Develop and disseminate thought leadership through white papers, reports, and presentations<br />
&bull; Gather, analyze, and synthesize information from internal and external sources<br />
&bull; Translate research findings from disparate arrays of facts into a coherent analysis of trends<br />
&bull; Collaborate with cross-functional project teams to determine what information is needed and how best to present the findings<br />
&bull; Organize and maintain a searchable archive of work produced by the research team<br />
&bull; Act as an insights evangelist to internal and external clients including Cloudmark employees, customers, partners, industry analysts and the media<br />
&bull; Determine critical knowledge gaps based on synthesizing internal data, industry knowledge, project needs, and Cloudmark&rsquo;s business goals<br />
&bull; Lead the translation of context research findings into actionable foundational insights and opportunity areas; communicate the insights and recommendations to internal and external customers and multidisciplinary teams and help to drive their application<br />
&bull; Speaking engagements at conferences and other industry opportunities</p>
<p>
Qualifications<br />
&bull; Experience uncovering, analyzing, and synthesizing qualitative and quantitative data centered ideally on the messaging security market<br />
&bull; Demonstrable understanding of and facility with secondary / context research, data mining, market / user research, a range of qualitative and quantitative research methods, and insight generation as well as the types of resources used to extract information<br />
&bull; A thorough, detail-oriented approach combined with an ability to discover new sources of information and developing new ways of packaging and sharing that information in ways that resonate with various audiences<br />
&bull; Excellent oral and written communication skills including the ability to construct and deliver compelling and succinct presentations, collateral and reports to internal and external teams<br />
&bull; Expert in PowerPoint and presentation-building, Excel, and Word<br />
&bull; Speaking to large audiences on security research and industry trends<br />
&bull; Experience mentoring junior staff<br />
&bull; Willingness to travel as needed</p>
<p>
Education<br />
&bull; Degree in Information Security, Computer Science, or other applicable field; or relevant work experience</p>
<p>
Experience<br />
&bull; 10+ years of relevant experience or equivalent combination of education and work experience</p>
<p>
Skills Required<br />
&bull; Strong technical communication skills, both written and verbal<br />
&bull; Effective time management and organizational skills<br />
&bull; Team player with the ability to work autonomously in a fast-paced, dynamic environment<br />
&bull; Investigative and analytical problem solving skills<br />
&bull; Inherent passion for information</p>
<p>
Travel:<br />
&bull; 25-35% for conferences, speaking engagements and office visits</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
