			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Cloudmark is a venture-backed, privately-held anti-spam technology company, headquartered in San Francisco, California, that produces high performance messaging security solutions to the world&rsquo;s largest ISPs, mobile and social networks. Our customers include over 100 of the world&#39;s largest Internet service providers and mobile network operators, including tier-1 operators in North America, Japan and Europe.</p>
<p>
<strong>Objective of Position</strong><br />
This person&#39;s primary responsibility will be to drive Cloudmark relationship, existing and new business for one or more Tier 1 Operator Customers / Prospects. This role would be key sales role on the team and be responsible for setting the sales strategy, leading account engagement, and directing the internal organizations in support of growing Cloudmark&rsquo;s wireless and wireline solution sales with Customer.</p>
<p>
This role requires an experience, seasoned, knowledgeable, strategic sales leader with skills on in-depth needs analysis, customized presentations, demonstrations, and delivery of written proposals to support carrier&rsquo;s needs. Candidate must be a self-starter, a collaborator and synthesizer; excellent communication and teamwork/leading skills; can work effectively with executive management, customers, various company departments and individual contributors. Candidate must also demonstrate full knowledge of the accounts, the ability to work in a fast-paced environment, which requires multitasking and efficient time management. Will be required to initiate and participate in both strategic and conceptual discussions, as well as address detailed/tactical activities.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Develop and execute sales strategies to profitably grow software and services revenue plan</li>
<li>
Lead sales negotiations with customers and partner with internal organizations to obtain required approvals. Ensure sales deals are closed that deliver the expected P&amp; L results</li>
<li>
Manage customer relationships on multiple levels with key stakeholders in the Customer&rsquo;s corporate organizations</li>
<li>
Exercise profit/loss authority for sales orders. Ensure business terms support cash collection targets</li>
<li>
Provide sales leadership to internal teams throughout the sales process. Ensure key project and customer requirements are understood and addressed</li>
<li>
Provide sales input in support of the growth planning process</li>
<li>
